From 2e96b8cc1842da38cf1f0456c7d265af20e1af70 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christopher Albert <albert@tugraz.at>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 2026 00:21:27 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] fortran: Add testcase [PR95163]

The reproducer from the bug report now gives a proper error on current
trunk instead of an ICE.  Add a testcase to prevent future regressions.

	PR fortran/95163

gcc/testsuite/ChangeLog:

	PR fortran/95163
	* gfortran.dg/gomp/pr95163.f90: New test.

Signed-off-by: Christopher Albert <albert@tugraz.at>
(cherry picked from commit 67431721378391be7cb774c789a8da10c0f827ee)
---
 gcc/testsuite/gfortran.dg/gomp/pr95163.f90 | 13 +++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 gcc/testsuite/gfortran.dg/gomp/pr95163.f90

diff --git a/gcc/testsuite/gfortran.dg/gomp/pr95163.f90 b/gcc/testsuite/gfortran.dg/gomp/pr95163.f90
new file mode 100644
index 000000000000..e64e9437b0ba
--- /dev/null
+++ b/gcc/testsuite/gfortran.dg/gomp/pr95163.f90
@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@
+! { dg-do compile }
+! PR fortran/95163
+! Contributed by John Donners <john.donners@eviden.com>
+!
+! ICE in gimplify_adjust_omp_clauses with map and firstprivate on same
+! variable.
+
+  integer :: i
+  i = 1
+!$omp target map(tofrom: i) firstprivate (i)  ! { dg-error "present on both data and map clauses" }
+  i = i + 1
+!$omp end target
+end
-- 
2.43.7


